title: One Direction are going head to head with KDA, Tinie Tempah and Katy B for No.1 - Music
text: One Direction are battling KDA, Katy B and Tinie Tempah for this week's number one.The London DJ's track 'Turn The Music Louder (Rumble)' featuring Katy B and Tinie Tempah is currently outselling 1D's 'Perfect' by just over 7,000 chart sales. If it can hold onto its position, the single will become KDA and Katy B's first number one and Tinie Tempah's seventh.Meanwhile, Canadian producer Sleepy Tom and Diplo are at three with 'Be Right There' after climbing 88 places.The Weeknd is at four with 'The Hills' while Ed Sheeran signee Jamie Lawson completes the Top 5 with 'Wasn't Expecting That'. Ben Haenow enters the charts at seven with his Kelly Clarkson duet 'Second Hand Heart' while Take That are at 20 with their new single 'Hey Boy'.Elsewhere, Nick Jonas's 'Levels' is up 13 places to 33, Taylor Swift's 'Wildest Dreams' climbs 23 places to 22 and Little Mix's 'Weird People' starts at 36.Over on the albums chart, Jamie Lawson's self-titled record is in the lead with double the sales of its closest competitor, Demi Lovato's Confident. Â© Getty Images / Frederick M Brown John Newman is at three with his second album Revolve while Nothing But Thieves are at four and Peter Andre's 10th album Come Fly with Me completes the Top 5.Scouting for Girls are at eight with their fourth album Still Thinking About You while Fightstar are eyeing up their first Top 10 album with Behind the Devil's Back at nine.Watch the music video for KDA's 'Turn the Music Louder (Rumble)' ft.
